# Repo-level Semgrep ignores. Anything matched here is excluded from
# `semgrep scan` runs. Used by the security orchestrator
# (`make baas-security-scan`).
#
# Rule of thumb: only ignore THIRD-PARTY paths or generated artifacts that we
# do not own. Never ignore project source code — fix the issue or annotate
# the specific line with `# nosemgrep:<rule-id>` + a comment explaining why.

# ── Build artifacts and dependency trees ──────────────────────────────────
node_modules/
**/node_modules/
dist/
**/dist/
build/
**/build/
.next/
**/.next/
coverage/
**/coverage/
playwright-report/
**/playwright-report/
test-results/
**/test-results/

# ── Virtual environments (Python venv for the doc translator) ─────────────
.venv/
.venv-translate/
**/.venv/
**/.venv-translate/
**/site-packages/

# ── Third-party / vendored code ───────────────────────────────────────────
vendor/
**/vendor/

# ── Generated / cached files ──────────────────────────────────────────────
**/.git/
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/.mypy_cache/
**/.pytest_cache/

# ── Security artifacts (own scan output, never reanalyse) ─────────────────
**/artifacts/security/

# ── Lock files (scanned separately by SCA tools) ──────────────────────────
**/package-lock.json
**/pnpm-lock.yaml
**/yarn.lock
**/Cargo.lock
